258 // $pname
259 CHAR *
260 ScriptEnginePseudoRegGetPname()
261 {
262 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
263 
264  HANDLE Handle = OpenProcess(
265  PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION | PROCESS_VM_READ,
266  FALSE,
267  GetCurrentProcessId() /* Current process */
268  );
269 
270  if (Handle)
271  {
272  CHAR CurrentModulePath[MAX_PATH] = {0};
273  if (GetModuleFileNameEx(Handle, 0, CurrentModulePath, MAX_PATH))
274  {
275 
276  //
277  // At this point, buffer contains the full path to the executable
278  //
279  CloseHandle(Handle);
280  return PathFindFileNameA(CurrentModulePath);
281  }
282  else
283  {
284  //
285  // error might be shown by GetLastError()
286  //
287  CloseHandle(Handle);
288  return NULL;
289  }
290  }
291 
292  //
293  // unable to get handle
294  //
295  return NULL;
296 
297 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
298 
299 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
300  return GetProcessNameFromEprocess(PsGetCurrentProcess());
301 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
302 }

502 //
503 // Check whether the address is valid or
504 //
505 BOOLEAN
506 ScriptEngineCheckAddressValidity(PUINT64 Address, UINT32 Length)
507 {
508 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
509 
510  //
511  // Actually, there is no way to check this validity as it causes cpu
512  // errors, so the only solution is using SEH which is stupid idea,
513  // sure we don't want to create SEH frame each time we need to check
514  // a function address, so I don't know what to do, let's return TRUE
515  // for now
516  //
517  return TRUE;
518 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
519 
520 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
521 
522  if (VirtualAddressToPhysicalAddress(Address) == 0)
523  {
524  return FALSE;
525  }
526  else
527  {
528  if (VirtualAddressToPhysicalAddress(Address + Length) == 0)
529  {
530  return FALSE;
531  }
532  else
533  {
534  return TRUE;
535  }
536  }
537 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
538 }

1043 // pause

1045 ScriptEngineFunctionPause(UINT64 Tag, BOOLEAN ImmediateMessagePassing, PGUEST_REGS GuestRegs, UINT64 Context)
1046 {
1047 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1048  ShowMessages("err, breaking is not possible in user-mode\n");
1049 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1050 
1051 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1052 
1053  //
1054  // pause(); function is only working when kernel debugger is working
1055  // it's not designed to work on vmi-mode (local debugging)
1056  //
1057  if (g_KernelDebuggerState)
1058  {
1059  DEBUGGER_TRIGGERED_EVENT_DETAILS ContextAndTag = {0};
1060  UINT32 CurrentProcessorIndex = KeGetCurrentProcessorNumber();
1061 
1062  if (g_GuestState[CurrentProcessorIndex].IsOnVmxRootMode)
1063  {
1064  //
1065  // The guest is already in vmx-root mode
1066  // Halt other cores
1067  //
1068  ContextAndTag.Tag = Tag;
1069  ContextAndTag.Context = Context;
1070 
1071  KdHandleBreakpointAndDebugBreakpoints(
1072  CurrentProcessorIndex,
1073  GuestRegs,
1074  DEBUGGEE_PAUSING_REASON_DEBUGGEE_EVENT_TRIGGERED,
1075  &ContextAndTag);
1076  }
1077  else
1078  {
1079  //
1080  // The guest is on vmx non-root mode, the first parameter
1081  // is context and the second parameter is tag
1082  //
1083  AsmVmxVmcall(VMCALL_VM_EXIT_HALT_SYSTEM_AS_A_RESULT_OF_TRIGGERING_EVENT, Context, Tag, 0);
1084  }
1085  }
1086  else
1087  {
1088  LogInfo("The 'pause();' function is called but you're not allowed to use it on vmi-mode (local debugging)");
1089  }
1090 
1091 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1092 }

1166 VOID
1167 ApplyFormatSpecifier(const CHAR * CurrentSpecifier, CHAR * FinalBuffer, PUINT32 CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat, PUINT32 CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer, UINT64 Val, UINT32 SizeOfFinalBuffer)
1168 {
1169  UINT32 TempBufferLen = 0;
1170  CHAR TempBuffer[50 + 1] = {
1171  0}; // Maximum uint64_t is 18446744073709551615 + 1 thus its 20 character
1172  // for maximum buffer + 1 end char null but we alloc 50 to be sure
1173 
1174  *CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat =
1175  *CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat + strlen(CurrentSpecifier);
1176  sprintf(TempBuffer, CurrentSpecifier, Val);
1177  TempBufferLen = strlen(TempBuffer);
1178 
1179  //
1180  // Check final buffer capacity
1181  //
1182  if (*CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer + TempBufferLen > SizeOfFinalBuffer)
1183  {
1184  //
1185  // Over passed buffer
1186  //
1187  return;
1188  }
1189 
1190  memcpy(&FinalBuffer[*CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer], TempBuffer, TempBufferLen);
1191 
1192  *CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer = *CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer + TempBufferLen;
1193 }

1195 size_t
1196 WcharToChar(const wchar_t * src, char * dest, size_t dest_len)
1197 {
1198  wchar_t Code;
1199  size_t i;
1200 
1201  i = 0;
1202 
1203  while (src[i] != '\0' && i < (dest_len - 1))
1204  {
1205  Code = src[i];
1206  if (Code < 128)
1207  dest[i] = (char)Code;
1208  else
1209  {
1210  dest[i] = '?';
1211  if (Code >= 0xD800 && Code <= 0xD8FF)
1212  {
1213  //
1214  // Lead surrogate, skip the next code unit, which is the trail
1215  //
1216  i++;
1217  }
1218  }
1219  i++;
1220  }
1221 
1222  return i - 1;
1223 }

1225 BOOLEAN
1226 ApplyStringFormatSpecifier(const CHAR * CurrentSpecifier, CHAR * FinalBuffer, PUINT32 CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat, PUINT32 CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer, UINT64 Val, BOOLEAN IsWstring, UINT32 SizeOfFinalBuffer)
1227 {
1228  UINT32 StringSize;
1229  wchar_t WstrBuffer[50];
1230  CHAR AsciiBuffer[sizeof(WstrBuffer) / 2];
1231  UINT32 StringSizeInByte; /* because of wide-char */
1232  UINT32 CountOfBlocks;
1233  UINT32 CountOfBytesToRead;
1234  UINT32 CopiedBlockLen;
1235 
1236  //
1237  // First we have to check if string is valid or not
1238  //
1239  if (!CheckIfStringIsSafe(Val, IsWstring))
1240  {
1241  return FALSE;
1242  }
1243 
1244  //
1245  // get the length of the string (format) identifier
1246  //
1247  *CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat += strlen(CurrentSpecifier);
1248 
1249  //
1250  // Get string len
1251  //
1252  StringSize = CustomStrlen(Val, IsWstring);
1253 
1254  //
1255  // Check final buffer capacity
1256  //
1257  if (*CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer + StringSize > SizeOfFinalBuffer)
1258  {
1259  //
1260  // Over passed buffer
1261  //
1262  return TRUE;
1263  }
1264 
1265  //
1266  // Move the buffer string into the target buffer
1267  //
1268  if (IsWstring)
1269  {
1270  //
1271  // Parse wstring
1272  //
1273  StringSizeInByte = StringSize * 2; /* because of wide-char */
1274 
1275  //
1276  // compute the ceiling
1277  //
1278  if (StringSizeInByte % sizeof(WstrBuffer) == 0)
1279  {
1280  CountOfBlocks = StringSizeInByte / sizeof(WstrBuffer);
1281  }
1282  else
1283  {
1284  CountOfBlocks = (StringSizeInByte / sizeof(WstrBuffer)) + 1;
1285  }
1286 
1287  for (size_t i = 0; i < CountOfBlocks; i++)
1288  {
1289  //
1290  // Zero the buffers
1291  //
1292  RtlZeroMemory(WstrBuffer, sizeof(WstrBuffer));
1293  RtlZeroMemory(AsciiBuffer, sizeof(AsciiBuffer));
1294 
1295  //
1296  // Check for the last block
1297  //
1298  if (i == CountOfBlocks - 1)
1299  {
1300  //
1301  // A portion of block
1302  //
1303 
1304 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1305  memcpy(WstrBuffer, (void *)(Val + (i * sizeof(WstrBuffer))), StringSizeInByte % sizeof(WstrBuffer));
1306 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1307 
1308 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1309  MemoryMapperReadMemorySafeOnTargetProcess(
1310  (void *)(Val + (i * sizeof(WstrBuffer))),
1311  WstrBuffer,
1312  StringSizeInByte % sizeof(WstrBuffer));
1313 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1314  }
1315  else
1316  {
1317  //
1318  // A complete block
1319  //
1320 
1321 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1322  memcpy(WstrBuffer, (void *)(Val + (i * sizeof(WstrBuffer))), sizeof(WstrBuffer));
1323 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1324 
1325 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1326  MemoryMapperReadMemorySafeOnTargetProcess(
1327  (void *)(Val + (i * sizeof(WstrBuffer))),
1328  WstrBuffer,
1329  sizeof(WstrBuffer));
1330 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1331  }
1332 
1333  //
1334  // Here we have the filled WstrBuffer
1335  // We should convert WstrBuffer to AsciiBuffer
1336  //
1337  CopiedBlockLen =
1338  WcharToChar(WstrBuffer, AsciiBuffer, sizeof(AsciiBuffer) + 1);
1339 
1340  //
1341  // Now we should move the AsciiBuffer to the target buffer
1342  // (when we filled AsciiBuffer the memory here is safe so we
1343  // can use memcpy in both user-mode and vmx-root mode)
1344  //
1345  memcpy(&FinalBuffer[*CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer], (void *)AsciiBuffer, CopiedBlockLen + 1);
1346 
1347  *CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer += CopiedBlockLen + 1;
1348  }
1349  }
1350  else
1351  {
1352  //
1353  // Parse string
1354  //
1355 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1356  memcpy(&FinalBuffer[*CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer], (void *)Val, StringSize);
1357 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1358 
1359 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1360  MemoryMapperReadMemorySafeOnTargetProcess(
1361  Val,
1362  &FinalBuffer[*CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer],
1363  StringSize);
1364 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1365 
1366  *CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer += StringSize;
1367  }
1368 
1369  return TRUE;
1370 }
1371 
1372 VOID
1373 ScriptEngineFunctionPrintf(PGUEST_REGS GuestRegs,
1374  ACTION_BUFFER ActionDetail,
1375  UINT64 * g_TempList,
1376  UINT64 * g_VariableList,
1377  UINT64 Tag,
1378  BOOLEAN ImmediateMessagePassing,
1379  char * Format,
1380  UINT64 ArgCount,
1381  PSYMBOL FirstArg,
1382  BOOLEAN * HasError)
1383 {
1384  //
1385  // The printf function
1386  //
1387 
1388  char FinalBuffer[PacketChunkSize] = {0};
1389  UINT32 CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer = 0;
1390  UINT32 CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat = 0;
1391  BOOLEAN WithoutAnyFormatSpecifier = TRUE;
1392 
1393  UINT64 Val;
1394  UINT32 Position;
1395  UINT32 LenOfFormats = strlen(Format) + 1;
1396  PSYMBOL Symbol;
1397 
1398  *HasError = FALSE;
1399 
1400  for (int i = 0; i < ArgCount; i++)
1401  {
1402  WithoutAnyFormatSpecifier = FALSE;
1403  Symbol = FirstArg + i;
1404 
1405  //
1406  // Address is either wstring (%ws) or string (%s)
1407  //
1408 
1409  Position = (Symbol->Type >> 32) + 1;
1410 
1411  SYMBOL TempSymbol = {0};
1412  memcpy(&TempSymbol, Symbol, sizeof(SYMBOL));
1413  TempSymbol.Type &= 0x7fffffff;
1414 
1415  Val = GetValue(GuestRegs, ActionDetail, g_TempList, g_VariableList, &TempSymbol);
1416 
1417  CHAR PercentageChar = Format[Position];
1418 
1419  /*
1420  printf("position = %d is %c%c \n", Position, PercentageChar,
1421  IndicatorChar1);
1422  */
1423 
1424  if (CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat != Position)
1425  {
1426  //
1427  // There is some strings before this format specifier
1428  // we should move it to the buffer
1429  //
1430  UINT32 StringLen = Position - CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat;
1431 
1432  //
1433  // Check final buffer capacity
1434  //
1435  if (CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer + StringLen < sizeof(FinalBuffer))
1436  {
1437  memcpy(&FinalBuffer[CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer],
1438  &Format[CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat],
1439  StringLen);
1440 
1441  CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat += StringLen;
1442  CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer += StringLen;
1443  }
1444  }
1445 
1446  //
1447  // Double check and apply
1448  //
1449  if (PercentageChar == '%')
1450  {
1451  //
1452  // Set first character of specifier
1453  //
1454  CHAR FormatSpecifier[5] = {0};
1455  FormatSpecifier[0] = '%';
1456 
1457  //
1458  // Read second char
1459  //
1460  CHAR IndicatorChar2 = Format[Position + 1];
1461 
1462  //
1463  // Check if IndicatorChar2 is 2 character long or more
1464  //
1465  if (IndicatorChar2 == 'l' || IndicatorChar2 == 'w' ||
1466  IndicatorChar2 == 'h')
1467  {
1468  //
1469  // Set second char in format specifier
1470  //
1471  FormatSpecifier[1] = IndicatorChar2;
1472 
1473  if (IndicatorChar2 == 'l' && Format[Position + 2] == 'l')
1474  {
1475  //
1476  // Set third character in format specifier "ll"
1477  //
1478  FormatSpecifier[2] = 'l';
1479 
1480  //
1481  // Set last character
1482  //
1483  FormatSpecifier[3] = Format[Position + 3];
1484  }
1485  else
1486  {
1487  //
1488  // Set last character
1489  //
1490  FormatSpecifier[2] = Format[Position + 2];
1491  }
1492  }
1493  else
1494  {
1495  //
1496  // It's a one char specifier (Set last character)
1497  //
1498  FormatSpecifier[1] = IndicatorChar2;
1499  }
1500 
1501  //
1502  // Apply the specifier
1503  //
1504  if (!strncmp(FormatSpecifier, "%s", 2))
1505  {
1506  //
1507  // for string
1508  //
1509  if (!ApplyStringFormatSpecifier(
1510  "%s",
1511  FinalBuffer,
1512  &CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat,
1513  &CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer,
1514  Val,
1515  FALSE,
1516  sizeof(FinalBuffer)))
1517  {
1518  *HasError = TRUE;
1519  return;
1520  }
1521  }
1522  else if (!strncmp(FormatSpecifier, "%ls", 3) ||
1523  !strncmp(FormatSpecifier, "%ws", 3))
1524  {
1525  //
1526  // for wide string (not important if %ls or %ws , only the length is
1527  // important)
1528  //
1529  if (!ApplyStringFormatSpecifier(
1530  "%ws",
1531  FinalBuffer,
1532  &CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat,
1533  &CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer,
1534  Val,
1535  TRUE,
1536  sizeof(FinalBuffer)))
1537  {
1538  *HasError = TRUE;
1539  return;
1540  }
1541  }
1542  else
1543  {
1544  ApplyFormatSpecifier(FormatSpecifier, FinalBuffer, &CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat, &CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer, Val, sizeof(FinalBuffer));
1545  }
1546  }
1547  }
1548 
1549  if (WithoutAnyFormatSpecifier)
1550  {
1551  //
1552  // Means that it's just a simple print without any format specifier
1553  //
1554  if (LenOfFormats < sizeof(FinalBuffer))
1555  {
1556  memcpy(FinalBuffer, Format, LenOfFormats);
1557  }
1558  }
1559  else
1560  {
1561  //
1562  // Check if there is anything after the last format specifier
1563  //
1564  if (LenOfFormats > CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat)
1565  {
1566  UINT32 RemainedLen =
1567  LenOfFormats - CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat;
1568 
1569  if (CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer + RemainedLen < sizeof(FinalBuffer))
1570  {
1571  memcpy(&FinalBuffer[CurrentPositionInFinalBuffer],
1572  &Format[CurrentProcessedPositionFromStartOfFormat],
1573  RemainedLen);
1574  }
1575  }
1576  }
1577 
1578 //
1579 // Print final result
1580 //
1581 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1582  printf("%s", FinalBuffer);
1583 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_USER_MODE
1584 
1585 #ifdef SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1586  LogSimpleWithTag(Tag, ImmediateMessagePassing, "%s", FinalBuffer);
1587 #endif // SCRIPT_ENGINE_KERNEL_MODE
1588 }

1590 UINT64
1591 GetRegValue(PGUEST_REGS GuestRegs, REGS_ENUM RegId)
1592 {
1593  switch (RegId)
1594  {
1595  case REGISTER_RAX:
1596  return GuestRegs->rax;
1597 
1598  break;
1599 
1600  case REGISTER_EAX:
1601  return (GuestRegs->rax & LOWER_32_BITS);
1602 
1603  break;
1604 
1605  case REGISTER_AX:
1606  return (GuestRegs->rax & LOWER_16_BITS);
1607 
1608  break;
1609 
1610  case REGISTER_AH:
1611  return (GuestRegs->rax & SECOND_LOWER_8_BITS) >> 8;
1612 
1613  break;
1614 
1615  case REGISTER_AL:

2539  case PSEUDO_REGISTER_TEB:

2541  case PSEUDO_REGISTER_IP:

2564 UINT64
2565 GetValue(PGUEST_REGS GuestRegs, ACTION_BUFFER ActionBuffer, UINT64 * g_TempList, UINT64 * g_VariableList, PSYMBOL Symbol)
2566 {
2567  switch (Symbol->Type)
2568  {
2569  case SYMBOL_ID_TYPE:
2570  return g_VariableList[Symbol->Value];
2571  case SYMBOL_NUM_TYPE:
2572  return Symbol->Value;
2573  case SYMBOL_REGISTER_TYPE:
2574  return GetRegValue(GuestRegs, (REGS_ENUM)Symbol->Value);
2575  case SYMBOL_PSEUDO_REG_TYPE:
2576  return GetPseudoRegValue(Symbol, ActionBuffer);
2577  case SYMBOL_TEMP_TYPE:
2578  return g_TempList[Symbol->Value];
2579  }
